{
  "work_slug": "alices-adventures-in-wonderland-by-lewis-carroll-5",
  "work_title": "Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (version 4)",
  "work_author": "Lewis Carroll",
  "audio_file": "audio-06",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/alices_adventures_1005_librivox/wonderland_06_carroll.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "06 - Pig and Pepper",
  "reader_name": "Eric Leach",
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.729,
  "page_num": 3,
  "page_total": 4,
  "page_start_sec": 497.46,
  "page_end_sec": 739.16,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 497.46,
      "end": 499.28,
      "text": "If I don't take this child away with me,"
    },
    {
      "start": 499.36,
      "end": 499.86,
      "text": "thought Alice,"
    },
    {
      "start": 500.18,
      "end": 501.88,
      "text": "they're sure to kill it in a day or two."
    },
    {
      "start": 502.784,
      "end": 504.26,
      "text": "Wouldn't it be murder to leave it behind?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 506.1,
      "end": 507.52,
      "text": "She said the last words out loud,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 507.7,
      "end": 509.42,
      "text": "and the little thing grunted in reply."
    },
    {
      "start": 510.24,
      "end": 511.9,
      "text": "It had left off sneezing by this time.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 512.96,
      "end": 513.52,
      "text": "Don't grunt,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 513.6,
      "end": 514.08,
      "text": "said Alice."
    },
    {
      "start": 514.3,
      "end": 516.48,
      "text": "That's not at all a proper way of expressing yourself."
    },
    {
      "start": 517.6,
      "end": 518.54,
      "text": "The baby grunted again,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 518.78,
      "end": 521.2,
      "text": "and Alice looked very anxiously into its face"
    },
    {
      "start": 521.34,
      "end": 522.82,
      "text": "to see what was the matter with it."
    },
    {
      "start": 523.21,
      "end": 526.22,
      "text": "There could be no doubt that it had a very turn-up nose,"
    },
    {
      "start": 526.46,
      "end": 528.34,
      "text": "much more like a snout than a real nose."
    },
    {
      "start": 528.92,
      "end": 529.34,
      "text": "Also,"
    },
    {
      "start": 529.42,
      "end": 531.8,
      "text": "its eyes were getting extremely small for a baby."
    },
    {
      "start": 532.53,
      "end": 533.08,
      "text": "Altogether,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 533.22,
      "end": 535.36,
      "text": "Alice did not like the look of the thing at all."
    },
    {
      "start": 535.94,
      "end": 537.52,
      "text": "But perhaps it was only sobbing,"
    },
    {
      "start": 537.54,
      "end": 537.9,
      "text": "she thought,"
    },
    {
      "start": 538.38,
      "end": 541.14,
      "text": "and looked into its eyes again to see if there were any tears."
    },
    {
      "start": 542.02,
      "end": 542.38,
      "text": "No,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 542.38,
      "end": 543.2,
      "text": "there were no tears."
    },
    {
      "start": 543.86,
      "end": 545.38,
      "text": "If you're going to turn into a pig,"
    },
    {
      "start": 545.44,
      "end": 545.74,
      "text": "my dear,"
    },
    {
      "start": 545.88,
      "end": 546.66,
      "text": "said Alice seriously,"
    },
    {
      "start": 546.96,
      "end": 548.42,
      "text": "I'll have nothing more to do with you,"
    },
    {
      "start": 548.46,
      "end": 548.86,
      "text": "mind now."
    },
    {
      "start": 550.17,
      "end": 552.38,
      "text": "The poor little thing sobbed again,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 552.54,
      "end": 553.28,
      "text": "or grunted,"
    },
    {
      "start": 553.36,
      "end": 554.72,
      "text": "it was impossible to say which,"
    },
    {
      "start": 555.26,
      "end": 557.34,
      "text": "and they went on for some while in silence."
    },
    {
      "start": 558.528,
      "end": 560.38,
      "text": "Alice was just beginning to think to herself,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 561.0,
      "end": 563.48,
      "text": "now what am I to do with this creature when I get it home,"
    },
    {
      "start": 563.58,
      "end": 565.48,
      "text": "when it grunted again so violently"
    },
    {
      "start": 565.74,
      "end": 568.02,
      "text": "that she looked down into its face in some alarm."
    },
    {
      "start": 568.36,
      "end": 570.86,
      "text": "This time there could be no mistake about it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 570.9,
      "end": 573.42,
      "text": "it was neither more nor less than a pig,"
    },
    {
      "start": 573.8,
      "end": 575.84,
      "text": "and she felt that it would be quite absurd for her to"
    },
    {
      "start": 575.98,
      "end": 576.76,
      "text": "carry it any further."
    },
    {
      "start": 577.94,
      "end": 579.48,
      "text": "So she set the little creature down,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 579.7,
      "end": 581.12,
      "text": "and felt quite relieved to see"
    },
    {
      "start": 581.12,
      "end": 583.02,
      "text": "it trot quietly away into the wood."
    },
    {
      "start": 583.9,
      "end": 584.74,
      "text": "If it had grown up,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 584.82,
      "end": 585.5,
      "text": "she said to herself,"
    },
    {
      "start": 586.02,
      "end": 586.38,
      "text": "it would have"
    },
    {
      "start": 586.38,
      "end": 587.96,
      "text": "made a dreadfully ugly child,"
    },
    {
      "start": 588.38,
      "end": 589.86,
      "text": "but it makes rather a handsome pig,"
    },
    {
      "start": 589.96,
      "end": 590.28,
      "text": "I think."
    },
    {
      "start": 591.4,
      "end": 592.32,
      "text": "And she began thinking",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 592.46,
      "end": 595.4,
      "text": "over other children she knew who might do very well as pigs,"
    },
    {
      "start": 595.54,
      "end": 597.04,
      "text": "and was just saying to herself,"
    },
    {
      "start": 597.74,
      "end": 599.74,
      "text": "if only I knew the right way to change them,"
    },
    {
      "start": 599.86,
      "end": 602.08,
      "text": "when she was a little startled by seeing the"
    },
    {
      "start": 602.26,
      "end": 605.24,
      "text": "Cheshire Cat sitting on a bough of a tree a few yards off."
    },
    {
      "start": 606.02,
      "end": 607.8,
      "text": "The cat only grinned when it saw Alice.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 608.36,
      "end": 609.42,
      "text": "It looked good-natured,"
    },
    {
      "start": 609.42,
      "end": 609.82,
      "text": "she thought,"
    },
    {
      "start": 609.94,
      "end": 612.74,
      "text": "still it had very long claws and a great many teeth,"
    },
    {
      "start": 613.22,
      "end": 615.28,
      "text": "so she felt that it ought to be treated with respect."
    },
    {
      "start": 616.832,
      "end": 617.54,
      "text": "Cheshire Puss,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 617.64,
      "end": 619.04,
      "text": "she began rather timidly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 619.04,
      "end": 621.44,
      "text": "as she did not at all know whether it would like the name."
    },
    {
      "start": 622.02,
      "end": 622.3,
      "text": "However,"
    },
    {
      "start": 622.48,
      "end": 624.1,
      "text": "it only grinned a little wider."
    },
    {
      "start": 625.42,
      "end": 625.66,
      "text": "Come,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 625.72,
      "end": 626.68,
      "text": "it's pleased so far,"
    },
    {
      "start": 626.8,
      "end": 627.24,
      "text": "thought Alice,"
    },
    {
      "start": 627.4,
      "end": 628.1,
      "text": "and she went on."
    },
    {
      "start": 629.0,
      "end": 629.56,
      "text": "Would you tell me,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 629.62,
      "end": 629.84,
      "text": "please,"
    },
    {
      "start": 630.02,
      "end": 631.36,
      "text": "which way I ought to go from here?"
    },
    {
      "start": 632.48,
      "end": 635.32,
      "text": "That depends a good deal on where you want to go,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 635.64,
      "end": 636.26,
      "text": "said the cat."
    },
    {
      "start": 636.92,
      "end": 638.22,
      "text": "I don't much care where,"
    },
    {
      "start": 638.5,
      "end": 639.0,
      "text": "said Alice."
    },
    {
      "start": 639.6,
      "end": 641.68,
      "text": "Then it doesn't matter which way you go,"
    },
    {
      "start": 641.9,
      "end": 642.66,
      "text": "said the cat."
    },
    {
      "start": 644.4,
      "end": 645.65,
      "text": "So long as I get somewhere,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 646.12,
      "end": 647.58,
      "text": "Alice added as an explanation."
    },
    {
      "start": 648.66,
      "end": 649.02,
      "text": "Oh,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 649.02,
      "end": 650.22,
      "text": "you're sure to do that,"
    },
    {
      "start": 650.44,
      "end": 651.02,
      "text": "said the cat,"
    },
    {
      "start": 651.14,
      "end": 652.98,
      "text": "if only you walk long enough."
    },
    {
      "start": 654.432,
      "end": 656.12,
      "text": "Alice felt that this could not be denied,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 656.4,
      "end": 657.8,
      "text": "so she tried another question."
    },
    {
      "start": 658.56,
      "end": 659.82,
      "text": "What sort of people live about here?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 661.22,
      "end": 662.26,
      "text": "In that direction,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 662.7,
      "end": 663.36,
      "text": "the cat said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 663.48,
      "end": 664.72,
      "text": "waving its right paw round,"
    },
    {
      "start": 664.92,
      "end": 666.14,
      "text": "lives a hatter"
    },
    {
      "start": 666.4,
      "end": 667.86,
      "text": "And in that direction,"
    },
    {
      "start": 668.06,
      "end": 669.08,
      "text": "waving the other paw,"
    },
    {
      "start": 669.32,
      "end": 670.76,
      "text": "lives a march hare"
    },
    {
      "start": 671.42,
      "end": 672.72,
      "text": "Visit either you like,"
    },
    {
      "start": 672.84,
      "end": 673.9,
      "text": "they're both mad"
    },
    {
      "start": 675.42,
      "end": 677.18,
      "text": "But I don't want to go among mad people,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 677.46,
      "end": 678.2,
      "text": "Alice remarked"
    },
    {
      "start": 678.58,
      "end": 679.38,
      "text": "Oh,"
    },
    {
      "start": 679.38,
      "end": 680.7,
      "text": "you can't help that,"
    },
    {
      "start": 681.18,
      "end": 682.22,
      "text": "said the cat"
    },
    {
      "start": 682.4,
      "end": 683.88,
      "text": "We're all mad here,"
    },
    {
      "start": 684.06,
      "end": 684.96,
      "text": "I'm mad,"
    },
    {
      "start": 685.32,
      "end": 686.22,
      "text": "you're mad"
    },
    {
      "start": 687.54,
      "end": 688.58,
      "text": "How do you know I'm mad,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 688.76,
      "end": 689.2,
      "text": "said Alice"
    },
    {
      "start": 690.48,
      "end": 691.7,
      "text": "You must be,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 691.92,
      "end": 692.56,
      "text": "said the cat,"
    },
    {
      "start": 692.76,
      "end": 694.46,
      "text": "or you wouldn't have come here."
    },
    {
      "start": 696.14,
      "end": 697.98,
      "text": "Alice didn't think that proved it at all.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 698.22,
      "end": 698.36,
      "text": "However,"
    },
    {
      "start": 698.54,
      "end": 699.14,
      "text": "she went on."
    },
    {
      "start": 700.36,
      "end": 701.66,
      "text": "And how do you know that you're mad?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 703.5,
      "end": 704.18,
      "text": "To begin with,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 704.512,
      "end": 705.04,
      "text": "said the cat,"
    },
    {
      "start": 705.2,
      "end": 706.58,
      "text": "a dog's not mad."
    },
    {
      "start": 706.98,
      "end": 707.52,
      "text": "You grant that?"
    },
    {
      "start": 708.44,
      "end": 709.1,
      "text": "I suppose so,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 709.3,
      "end": 709.76,
      "text": "said Alice."
    },
    {
      "start": 710.4,
      "end": 710.78,
      "text": "Well,"
    },
    {
      "start": 710.78,
      "end": 711.12,
      "text": "then,"
    },
    {
      "start": 711.36,
      "end": 712.26,
      "text": "the cat went on."
    },
    {
      "start": 712.46,
      "end": 712.78,
      "text": "You see,"
    },
    {
      "start": 712.92,
      "end": 717.16,
      "text": "a dog growls when it's angry and wags its tail when it's pleased."
    },
    {
      "start": 717.68,
      "end": 720.42,
      "text": "Now I growl when I'm pleased,"
    },
    {
      "start": 720.78,
      "end": 722.7,
      "text": "and wag my tail when I'm angry."
    },
    {
      "start": 723.32,
      "end": 724.82,
      "text": "Therefore I'm mad."
    },
    {
      "start": 726.5,
      "end": 727.62,
      "text": "I call it purring,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 727.62,
      "end": 728.36,
      "text": "not growling,"
    },
    {
      "start": 728.38,
      "end": 728.94,
      "text": "said Alice."
    },
    {
      "start": 729.984,
      "end": 730.94,
      "text": "Call it what you like,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 731.264,
      "end": 731.8,
      "text": "said the cat."
    },
    {
      "start": 732.1,
      "end": 734.12,
      "text": "Do you play croquet with the queen today?"
    },
    {
      "start": 735.5,
      "end": 737.28,
      "text": "I should like it very much,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 737.34,
      "end": 737.76,
      "text": "said Alice,"
    },
    {
      "start": 737.86,
      "end": 739.16,
      "text": "but I haven't been invited yet."
    }
  ]
}